<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-21 10:34 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2694 &Cx1f; taf-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SPORTS-NYT-BUDGET &LR;      11-21 0666
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPORTS-NYT-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
 Attn Sports Editors:  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sports stories in sight at this hour from The New York Times
News Service for use in papers of Sunday, Nov. 22:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FEATURE STORY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKN-BULLS-FLOYD (Deerfield, Ill.) _ Some 35 cardboard boxes,
many already sagging under their own weight, are piled high against
a wall outside the coach's office on the second floor of the Berto
Center, the Chicago Bulls' training facility. They have occupied
that spot for nearly three months, and belong to a man who is, more
or less, neither here nor there. He is Tim Floyd, Basketball's Man
Without a Definite Capacity. He is either the new coach of the
World Champion Chicago Bulls and successor to Phil Jackson, or he
is not. He is either the team's director of basketball operations,
a new Bulls' designation, or he is not. He is either their new
sweeper of the equipment room, or he is not. By Ira Berkow.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBA-ANDERSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ Dave Anderson sports column on
the possible sale of the Yankees to Cablevision.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-ARATON-COLUMN (New York) _ Harvey Araton sports column on
the Chase tennis championships.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ George Vecsey sports column on
Tito Landrum, an outfielder turned valedictorian. By George Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-LIPSYTE-COLUMN (Undated) _ Robert Lipsyte sports column on
Pete Harnisch, a reluctant role model.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COLLEGE FOOTBALL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBC-TENN-KY (Knoxville, Tenn.) _ Undefeated Tennessee Vols host
Kentucky. By Joe Drape.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UCLA-USC (Pasadena, Calif.) _ Undefeated UCLA vs. crosstown
rival Southern California. By Ed Guzman.
</P>
<P>
