<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Nov. 22, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact James Laurin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   LAUSD-GIFTED (Los Angeles) _ The Los Angeles Board of
Education's push to raise teacher salaries and begin tutoring and
other programs means they will have to renege on a promise to help
gifted children. Parents have fought for three years to improve
programs for gifted and highly gifted students in the LAUSD _ the
one uncontested shining star in the district. By Terri Hardy. (Will
move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
