<P>
   CLINTON-SEOUL _ Holding out the prospect of a new dawn for one
of the world's last remaining pariah states, President Clinton lent
a dramatic endorsement Saturday to Seoul's efforts to build new
partnerships with communist North Korea. He also repeated his call
on North Korea to open a suspected nuclear materials site to U.S.
inspectors and to end ballistic missile test launches. (Deans, Cox
News Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MONICA-SEOUL _ President Clinton said Saturday at a press
conference in Korea that he is paying a price for the Lewinsky
affair whether lawmakers discipline him further or not. He said
however it was not his place to suggest a course of Congressional
action. (Deans, Cox News Service) MOVED
