<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   VOINO _ EAST LIVERPOOL, Ohio _ A $160 million hazardous waste
incinerator beside the Ohio River, a now defunct state-funded
pollution monitoring agency, a permit for a landfill linked to a
new county jail project, and a lobbyist with ties to Gov. George
Voinovich's brother would all seem on the surface to have little in
common. But federal investigators are examining them all in an
exhaustive yearlong probe before a grand jury in Cincinnati that
shows no signs of ending any time soon. (Bennish/McCall , Dayton
Daily News) 45. WITH TIMELINE. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GUNS _ Sporting goods stores and other shops selling guns are
bracing for crowds and complaints this month as shoppers try to
beat a federal law that goes into effect Nov. 30. On that date,
potential buyers of handguns, rifles and shotguns must undergo a
background check to see if they are permitted to buy a gun.
(Morris/Grieco, Dayton Daily News). 32. WITH PHOTO, glance box (3.6
inches) with highlights of the law. MOVED
</P>
