<HEADLINE>
VAUGHN AND LA: MIXED SIGNALS? 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By NICK CAFARDO  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Will the Los Angeles Dodgers step up to the plate with an offer
for Mo Vaughn? Maybe, but landing the free agent first baseman
isn't general manager Kevin Malone's top priority.
</P>
<P>
   ``I had heard they were going to make me an offer Friday, but I
haven't heard from my agents yet,'' Vaughn said Saturday. ``I know
they've been interested from the beginning, but they've been trying
to do some things with their roster.''
</P>
<P>
   However, the Dodgers are concentrating on Randy Johnson, who
visited Dodger Stadium Saturday and anticipates an offer. Any
notion that a Los Angeles pitch to Vaughn is imminent is incorrect.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've had discussions with his agents, but we've not indicated
we will make an offer,'' Malone told the Los Angeles Times. ``We're
not even close to making an offer.''
</P>
<P>
   Asked if an offer to Vaughn may be made, Malone said, ``I guess
that's a possibility down the road.''
</P>
<P>
   The Anaheim Angels have offered Vaughn six years and $79
million, and Vaughn thought the Arizona Diamondbacks might get into
the mix if they're out of the running for center fielder Bernie
Williams.
</P>
<P>
   ``It really didn't matter whether it was one team or 20 teams
after me,'' said Vaughn. ``I just wanted a situation where the team
that was after me made it very clear they wanted me. The Angels
have done that. They've been great throughout the whole process.
They haven't put any time limits on any of this and they stepped to
the plate big-time.''
</P>
<P>
   Vaughn said he hasn't spoken to anyone from the Red Sox since
they made their final offer to him in Naples, Fla., a week and a
half ago.
</P>
<P>
   Vaughn said he wasn't disappointed that no Eastern team had made
an offer to date.
</P>
<P>
   ``I appreciate the ones that I do have,'' he said. ``This thing
has taken on the course I thought it would after the Red Sox
situation ended. We're not looking to accelerate this or try to
twist anyone's arm. We're being patient. I'm just sitting here at
home waiting. I'm working out and getting ready for the next
season.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
